Attribution

sequoia-boost is an independent, from-scratch reimplementation of the XGBoost
gradient boosting library in Rust:

    XGBoost — https://github.com/dmlc/xgboost
    Copyright the XGBoost Contributors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

sequoia-boost reimplements XGBoost's algorithms (the regularized second-order
boosting objective, exact/approx/histogram tree construction, objectives,
metrics, constraints, DART, gblinear, and TreeSHAP) from their public
descriptions and papers. It does not incorporate XGBoost's source code.

"XGBoost" is used only descriptively — to indicate algorithmic lineage and
result compatibility — and is a name of the DMLC / XGBoost project, not of this
crate. This project is not affiliated with or endorsed by the XGBoost project.
